content.thinking:
This is very important! `AuthStorage.create(authPath)`:

```javascript
static create(authPath) {
    return new AuthStorage(new FileAuthStorageBackend(authPath ?? join(getAgentDir(), "auth.json")));
}
```

When called with no args (as in `runSubagent`), `authPath` is `undefined`, so it falls back to `join(getAgentDir(), "auth.json")` which is `~/.pi/agent/auth.json`.

So `AuthStorage.create()` in `runSubagent` DOES load from the default auth.json file. If the user has API keys configured there, the auth storage would have them.

